  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "This method allowed the researcher to follow a set of predetermined questions while also providing the flexibility to probe deeper into areas of interest or clarify responses, ensuring a richer understanding of student experiences (Magaldi & Berler, 2020).",
    "Each interview was recorded using digital audio recording software on the researcher's tablet computer.",
    "The recordings were then transcribed automatically using digital transcription software and subsequently reviewed and manually corrected to address any errors in the transcription process.",
    "The transcribed interview data were subjected to thematic analysis, a method used to identify, analyze, and report patterns or themes within qualitative data (Attride-Stirling, 2001).",
    "Thematic analysis is particularly useful for describing and interpreting recurring themes within a dataset, offering a structured approach to understanding interviewees' perspectives (Braun & Clarke, 2006)."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "This method allowed the researcher to follow a set of predetermined questions while also providing the flexibility to probe deeper into areas of interest or clarify responses, ensuring a richer understanding of student experiences (Magaldi & Berler, 2020).",
